	h2 Things to do when the talks are over
	ol

		li Tourism
			p.
				The province of Palencia, including the city, has a large history reflected in many of #[a(href="http://www.visitarpalencia.com/?gclid=CMm7wKf6grsCFW_JtAod02gAwQ#%21castillos") castles], monuments, museums, #[a(href="http://www.visitarpalencia.com/?gclid=CMm7wKf6grsCFW_JtAod02gAwQ#%21monumentos-religiosos") churches] (in particular, many #[a(href="http://www.palenciaturismo.es/contenido/c3add75b-d5f4-11de-b283-fb9baaa14523?turistico=225c1d0d-a847-11de-a3d3-fb9baaa14523&amp;seccion=fbc4aa8b-d5f4-11de-b283-fb9baaa14523&amp;posicion=2&amp;lang=en") romanesque churches], archeological sites (with a few remarkable #[a(href="http://www.palenciaturismo.es/contenido/c3622849-d5f4-11de-b283-fb9baaa14523?seccion=fbb76418-d5f4-11de-b283-fb9baaa14523&amp;turistico=2d375970-a847-11de-a3d3-fb9baaa14523&amp;posicion=1") roman villas], specially the #[a(href="http://www.villaromanalaolmeda.com/") Villa de la Olmeda], highly recommendable), #[a(href="http://www.visitarpalencia.com/?gclid=CMm7wKf6grsCFW_JtAod02gAwQ#%21casas-y-palacios") palaces] etc.
			p.
				See, for instance:
			ul
				li #[a(href="http://www.palenciaturismo.es/portada?lang=en") Tourism in Palencia]
				li #[a(href="http://www.turismocastillayleon.com/turismocyl/en") Tourism in Castilla y León]
				li #[a(href="http://www.turismocastillayleon.com/turismocyl/en") A guide of castles and archeological sites of Castilla y León]
				li #[a(href="http://www.castillosdepalencia.es/index.html") A guide of castles in Palencia's province]

		li Hiking/biking
			p.
				The province is full of open spaces (partly because of the low population density) through which one can run, hike, bike etc. There many interesting routes in the northern mountains which range from easy family hikes to extreme climbing. The #[a(href="http://www.canaldecastilla.org/index.php") Channel of Castile], 170 Kms long, passes by the city and has very nice car-free tracks at each side where one can walrk, run or bike. 
			p.
				See, for instance:
			ul
				li #[a(href="http://www.montaña-palentina.com/") The northern mountain region (Montaña Palentina)]
				li #[a(href="http://www.palenciaturismo.es/contenido/c416d276-d5f4-11de-b283-fb9baaa14523?seccion=fbd3026e-d5f4-11de-b283-fb9baaa14523&seccionActual=0cafe08e-d5f5-11de-b283-fb9baaa14523&lang=en") The Montaña Palentina (English page)]
				li #[a(href="http://www.turismocastillayleon.com/cm/turcyl/tkContent?pgseed=1189159967451&amp;idContent=513814&amp;locale=es_ES&amp;textOnly=false") Hiking routes]
				li #[a(href="http://www.wikirutas.es/rutas/Castilla_y_Leon/Palencia/") Wikirutas: hiking routes]
				li #[a(href="http://es.senderators.com/rutas-senderismo:r:palencia") Senderator: hiking routes]
				li #[a(href="http://es.wikiloc.com/rutas/mountain-bike/espana/castilla-y-leon/palencia") Wikiloc: routes for mountain bikes]
		li Running
			p.
				For those of you interested in exercising, the organization will publish here some possible routes, easily accessible from the hotels and car-free.
		li Social life
			p.
				The city has a bar/cafeteria/restaurant for every 134 inhabitants and much of its social life takes place there. Some tips:		   	
